</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="5">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="5">
The epithet &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Awad" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Platygastridae" genus="Synopeas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Synopeas valavala" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valavala">Synopeas valavala</taxonomicName>
&quot; is Maenge for &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Macaranga" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Macaranga" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Macaranga</taxonomicName>
&quot; (Ross, 2008) and refers to the identity of the gall host plant. The name is to be treated as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="5" type="plant associations">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="5">Plant associations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="5">
Reared from round, fuzzy galls on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Macaranga" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Macaranga strigosa" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strigosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="5">Macaranga strigosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Macaranga" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Euphorbiaceae</taxonomicName>
) [GALL357].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
